However, if the allocation for `key->x` fails (i.e., `key->x` is `NULL`), this line will not be executed. But if the allocation for `key->y` fails after `key->x` has been successfully allocated, the function will attempt to free `key->x` again when it jumps to the error handling section. This leads to a double free vulnerability, where the same memory is freed twice, which can cause undefined behavior, crashes, or security vulnerabilities.

### The Modification

The modification changes the line in the error handling section to:

```c
